<font color="#FF0000">GOING READ ONLY MODE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Oct 19 21:25:36 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I originally started this thread to give us a place to duke it out, outside of the mainstream. Since then it has undergone a variety of changes, not all good, not all welcomed,  but that is America.<br><br>
However, I do not stomach anyone posting in anothers name, as has been done to me.  Referring to another male as someone's &quot;bitch&quot; is not in my lexicon, and more of a jailhouse or prison language.  Furthermore, while the imposter who attacked Artur was good, he, or she, failed to use the &quot;code&quot; word after his or her name, that I had e mailed Arthur about earlier. Plus I wasn't even on line that day.  Since then we now have anonomous posters, religious posters, angry posters, etc. etc.  What I wanted to avoid is what has happened. This thread, and others, have become a barnyard of animals, and the real issues are gone, and the real contributors are leaving, or have already left.<br><br>
When I have flamed in the past, I have acknowledged it, and apologized when necessary. I am only human, despite what some of you think. I also have endured one sided attacks and slurs from other individuals, and calls of being a coward, a commie, and other not so nice terms. Why? <br><br>
Because I am was anti-war and a protestor? To some I think so. To others, no, I think they appreciate that I was lucky to see the fraud of Viet Nam before they did, and I was just damn lucky to avoid the jungle.<br><br>
But when it comes to imposters, this is beyond hatred and anger. This is intentionally designed to destroy, to further hatred, to further needless fights, and it is pathological.<br><br>
I am tired of the name calling, of being labled a commie, or a coward (I am neither) and I am sorry that Arthur was likewise attacked, even sorrier that it was done in my name.<br><br>
To ensure that it is me, should I ever post here again, I will email as many of you as I can b/c at the same time, with verifying words, to prove it is me. I have never been ashamed of what my thoughts are, now I am.  If I am the lighting rod for all the kooks and wierdo's that seem to be coming out of the woodwork, then I will quietly retire and cease this relationship. I think you guys, and ladies,  those of you with PTSD, those of you with real combat survival, those of you who were spit on, need this site more than I do.  <br><br>
Protestors had their own hell to endure, but I never said it was a competition between us. Far from it. And being a C.O. was quite a bit different than being a draft evader, something that many of you never realized before.  To see the likes of Tom Dier pulling out breaks my heart, as he may be the last of the level headed posters (poster, not protestor). <br><br>
I may disagree with many of you, and I do, and esp. dislike one of you in particular, probably because of my inability to get that person to alter one inch of his thinking, which I blame myself for, but I have never used the type of anger and hatred, or see the need for such, as was done in my name, and I do not want some sick psycho who is hiding out there getting away with it again.  By b/c I will cc this message to one of &quot;the pack&quot; so verification can be achieved, and you will know it is me.  Meanwhile, I will go to read only mode for awhile.   Good Luck and God Bless.<br><br>
Doc Spatz 
